1
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:07,800
<i>CAPTAIN'S LOG,</i>
<i>STARDATE 2947.3.</i>

2
00:00:07,925 --> 00:00:10,719
<i>WE HAVE BEEN THROUGH</i>
<i>A SEVERE ION STORM.</i>

3
00:00:10,845 --> 00:00:12,304
<i>ONE CREWMAN IS DEAD.</i>

4
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:15,056
<i>THE SHIP'S DAMAGE</i>
<i>IS CONSIDERABLE.</i>

5
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:16,976
<i>I HAVE ORDERED</i>
<i>A NONSCHEDULED LAYOVER</i>

6
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,854
<i>ON STARBASE 11</i>
<i>FOR REPAIRS.</i>

7
00:00:19,979 --> 00:00:21,647
<i>A FULL REPORT OF DAMAGES</i>
<i>WAS MADE</i>

8
00:00:21,772 --> 00:00:26,318
<i>TO THE COMMANDING OFFICER</i>
<i>OF STARBASE 11--</i>
<i>COMMODORE STONE.</i>

9
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:31,699
MAINTENANCE,
SECTION 18.

10
00:00:31,824 --> 00:00:33,742
THE SECTION IS WORKING
ON THE<i> INTREPID.</i>

11
00:00:33,868 --> 00:00:39,498
RESCHEDULE. THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
IS ON PRIORITY 1.

12
00:00:39,623 --> 00:00:42,417
THAT MAKES THREE TIMES
YOU'VE READ IT, JIM.

13
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:43,961
IS THERE AN ERROR?

14
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:46,463
NO.

15
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,465
BUT THE DEATH
OF THE CREWMAN...

16
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:53,261
REGULATIONS, CAPTAIN.

17
00:00:53,387 --> 00:00:55,472
AND THE EXTRACT FROM
YOUR SHIP'S COMPUTER LOG

18
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:58,517
CONFIRMING THIS
SWORN DEPOSITION?

19
00:00:58,642 --> 00:00:59,768
KIRK TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

20
00:00:59,894 --> 00:01:01,186
[UHURA]
<i>BRIDGE HERE.</i>
<i>GO AHEAD, CAPTAIN.</i>

21
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:03,981
WHERE'S MR. SPOCK WITH
THAT COMPUTER LOG EXTRACT?

22
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:06,107
HE SHOULD
HAVE BEEN THERE
10 MINUTES AGO, SIR.

23
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,484
KIRK OUT.

24
00:01:07,609 --> 00:01:08,527
IT'S A GREAT PITY.

25
00:01:08,652 --> 00:01:09,862
THE SERVICE CAN'T
AFFORD

26
00:01:09,987 --> 00:01:10,905
TO LOSE MEN
LIKE LIEUTENANT
COMMANDER FINNEY.

27
00:01:11,030 --> 00:01:12,072
I AGREE.

28
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:14,491
I WAITED UNTIL
THE LAST POSSIBLE MOMENT.

29
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:17,160
WE WERE ON RED ALERT,
THE STORM GOT WORSE.

30
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:19,287
I HAD TO JETTISON
THE POD.

31
00:01:28,087 --> 00:01:29,882
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG,
MR. SPOCK?

32
00:01:30,007 --> 00:01:31,675
CAPTAIN...

33
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:32,384
I BELIEVE--

34
00:01:32,509 --> 00:01:33,844
I'LL TAKE THAT.

35
00:01:41,769 --> 00:01:42,436
JAME.

36
00:01:42,561 --> 00:01:44,229
THERE YOU ARE.

37
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:48,067
I JUST WANTED ONE MORE
LOOK AT YOU--THE MAN
WHO KILLED MY FATHER.

38
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:49,401
THAT'S NOT SO.
HE WAS MY FRIEND.

39
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:50,736
YOUR FRIEND?

40
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:52,613
YOU HATED HIM
ALL YOUR LIFE!

41
00:01:52,738 --> 00:01:55,657
THAT'S WHY
YOU KILLED HIM,
YOU MURDERER!

42
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:56,700
YOU MURDERER!

43
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:59,912
YOU MURDERER!

44
00:02:00,037 --> 00:02:01,246
JAME.

45
00:02:05,042 --> 00:02:07,044
MR. SPOCK,

46
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:08,712
WOULD YOU PLEASE...

47
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:16,011
MISS FINNEY,
COME WITH ME,
PLEASE.

48
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:17,930
CAPTAIN KIRK,

49
00:02:18,055 --> 00:02:20,265
YOU SAY YOU JETTISONED
THE POD AFTER THE RED ALERT?

50
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,309
YOU HAVE
MY SWORN DEPOSITION.

51
00:02:22,434 --> 00:02:23,811
THEN, CAPTAIN,
I MUST PRESUME

52
00:02:23,936 --> 00:02:26,563
YOU HAVE COMMITTED
WILLFUL PERJURY.

53
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:29,232
THIS EXTRACT FROM
YOUR COMPUTER LOG SAYS
YOU JETTISONED THE POD

54
00:02:29,357 --> 00:02:31,735
BEFORE GOING
TO RED ALERT.

55
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,821
CONSIDER YOURSELF
CONFINED TO THE BASE.

56
00:02:33,946 --> 00:02:35,280
AN OFFICIAL INQUIRY
WILL DETERMINE

57
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:37,240
WHETHER A GENERAL
COURT-MARTIAL IS IN ORDER.

58
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:48,961
<i>SPACE-- THE FINAL FRONTIER.</i>

59
00:02:49,086 --> 00:02:52,840
<i>THESE ARE THE VOYAGES</i>
<i>OF THE STARSHIP ENTERPRISE.</i>

60
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:54,549
<i>ITS FIVE-YEAR MISSION--</i>

61
00:02:54,675 --> 00:02:58,137
<i>TO EXPLORE STRANGE</i>
<i>NEW WORLDS...</i>

62
00:02:58,261 --> 00:03:01,890
<i>TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE</i>
<i>AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS...</i>

63
00:03:02,016 --> 00:03:05,268
<i>TO BOLDLY GO</i>
<i>WHERE NO MAN</i>
<i>HAS GONE BEFORE.</i>

64
00:03:39,053 --> 00:03:42,347
<i>CAPTAIN'S LOG,</i>
<i>STARDATE 2948.5.</i>

65
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:45,851
<i>STARSHIP</i> ENTERPRISE
<i>REMAINS IN ORBIT</i>
<i>AROUND STARBASE 11.</i>

66
00:03:45,976 --> 00:03:48,062
<i>FULL REPAIR</i>
<i>IS IN PROGRESS.</i>

67
00:03:48,187 --> 00:03:50,564
<i>I HAVE BEEN ORDERED</i>
<i>TO STAND BY ON STARBASE 11</i>

68
00:03:50,689 --> 00:03:53,400
<i>UNTIL THE INQUIRY</i>
<i>INTO THE DEATH OF</i>
<i>LIEUTENANT COMMANDER FINNEY</i>

69
00:03:53,525 --> 00:03:55,152
<i>CAN BE CONDUCTED.</i>

70
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,237
<i>I'M CONFIDENT</i>
<i>OF THE OUTCOME.</i>

71
00:03:57,362 --> 00:03:59,322
TIMOTHY,
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU

72
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:03,326
SINCE THE VULCANIAN
EXPEDITION.

73
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:06,580
WELL, I SEE
OUR GRADUATING CLASS
FROM THE ACADEMY

74
00:04:06,705 --> 00:04:08,165
IS WELL REPRESENTED.

75
00:04:08,289 --> 00:04:12,753
ARGAN, HELLER...

76
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:14,129
HOW YOU DOING, MIKE?

77
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:16,256
I'LL GET BY, JIM.

78
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:19,218
I UNDERSTAND
YOU'RE LAYING OVER
FOR REPAIRS.

79
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:20,552
BIG JOB?

80
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,929
COUPLE OF DAYS.

81
00:04:22,054 --> 00:04:23,805
YOU MOVING OUT THEN?

82
00:04:23,931 --> 00:04:25,348
IN A HURRY TO SEE ME GO?

83
00:04:25,473 --> 00:04:26,767
OH, I JUST WONDERED
HOW LONG IT WOULD
TAKE YOU

84
00:04:26,892 --> 00:04:29,978
TO GET A NEW
RECORDS OFFICER.

85
00:04:30,104 --> 00:04:31,312
YOU CAN TALK
PLAINER THAN THAT.

86
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:32,981
I CAN,

87
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:35,567
BUT I THINK
THE POINT'S
BEEN MADE.

88
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:36,985
BEN WAS A FRIEND
OF OURS.

89
00:04:37,111 --> 00:04:37,611
COME ON, JIM,
LET'S GO.

90
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:41,448
NO, GO ON. FINISH.

91
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:44,409
BEN WAS A FRIEND
OF YOURS, AND...

92
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:46,453
JIM.

93
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:47,788
GO ON.

94
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:49,123
I'M WAITING
TO HEAR THE REST.

95
00:04:49,248 --> 00:04:52,834
WHY DON'T
YOU TELL US?

96
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:56,130
WHAT WOULD BE THE POINT?

97
00:04:56,255 --> 00:05:03,095
YOU'VE ALREADY
MADE UP YOUR MINDS.

98
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,721
EXCUSE ME, BONES.

99
00:05:15,107 --> 00:05:16,483
IF YOU HAVE ANY DOUBT,

100
00:05:16,608 --> 00:05:19,278
THAT WAS INDEED
CAPTAIN JAMES KIRK
OF THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

101
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:20,654
YES, I KNOW.

102
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:21,905
ARE YOU
A FRIEND OF HIS?

103
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:25,450
IN THESE TRYING TIMES,
ONE OF THE FEW.

104
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:27,035
DR. LEONARD McCOY.

105
00:05:27,161 --> 00:05:28,036
AND YOU?

106
00:05:28,162 --> 00:05:29,412
AREEL SHAW.

107
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:31,123
AND I'M A FRIEND,
TOO...

108
00:05:31,248 --> 00:05:32,457
AN OLD ONE.

109
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:35,669
ALL OF MY OLD FRIENDS
LOOK LIKE DOCTORS.

110
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:38,005
ALL OF HIS LOOK
LIKE YOU.

111
00:05:38,130 --> 00:05:39,798
WELL, YOU MIGHT AS WELL
JOIN ME FOR A DRINK.

112
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:41,133
WITH THIS INQUIRY
COMING UP,

113
00:05:41,258 --> 00:05:43,093
HE'S GOING TO NEED
ALL THE FRIENDS
HE CAN GET.

114
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:47,139
[CLICK]

115
00:05:48,849 --> 00:05:50,433
<i>RECORDING INQUIRY.</i>

116
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:52,644
<i>MATTER-- CAPTAIN KIRK,</i>
<i>JAMES T.</i>

117
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,729
<i>SUBJECT--</i>
<i>CIRCUMSTANCES OF DEATH,</i>

118
00:05:54,855 --> 00:05:57,274
<i>LIEUTENANT</i>
<i>COMMANDER FINNEY,</i>
<i>BENJAMIN.</i>

119
00:05:57,398 --> 00:06:00,110
THIS INQUIRY TO DETERMINE
WHETHER A GENERAL
COURT-MARTIAL

120
00:06:00,235 --> 00:06:02,904
SHOULD BE CONVENED
AGAINST CAPTAIN KIRK.

121
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:07,742
THE CHARGES OF PERJURY
AND CULPABLE NEGLIGENCE.

122
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:10,287
READY.

123
00:06:10,411 --> 00:06:11,746
LET US BEGIN
WITH YOUR RELATIONSHIP

124
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,665
WITH COMMANDER FINNEY.

125
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:16,251
YOU KNEW HIM FOR
A LONG TIME, DIDN'T YOU?

126
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:18,712
YES. HE WAS
AN INSTRUCTOR
AT THE ACADEMY

127
00:06:18,837 --> 00:06:19,754
WHEN I WAS
A MIDSHIPMAN.

128
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,839
THAT DIDN'T STAND
IN THE WAY

129
00:06:20,964 --> 00:06:22,924
OF OUR BEGINNING
A CLOSE FRIENDSHIP.

130
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:24,592
HIS DAUGHTER JAME,
WHO WAS HERE LAST
NIGHT,

131
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,345
WAS NAMED AFTER ME.

132
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:29,014
IT'S COMMON KNOWLEDGE
THAT SOMETHING HAPPENED
TO YOUR FRIENDSHIP.

133
00:06:29,139 --> 00:06:30,431
IT'S NO SECRET.

134
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:33,392
WE WERE ASSIGNED
TO THE SAME SHIP
SOME YEARS LATER.

135
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:35,729
I RELIEVED HIM
ON WATCH ONCE

136
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:37,814
AND FOUND A CIRCUIT
OPEN TO THE ATOMIC
MATTER PILES

137
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:39,774
THAT SHOULD'VE
BEEN CLOSED.

138
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:40,859
ANOTHER
FIVE MINUTES,

139
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:42,527
IT COULD HAVE
BLOWN UP THE SHIP.

140
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:45,780
<i>SHIP NOMENCLATURE--</i>
<i>SPECIFY.</i>

141
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:49,784
UNITED STARSHIP
<i>REPUBLIC,</i>
<i>NUMBER 1371.</i>

142
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:51,870
CONTINUE.

143
00:06:51,995 --> 00:06:53,663
I CLOSED THE SWITCH

144
00:06:53,788 --> 00:06:55,582
AND LOGGED
THE INCIDENT.

145
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:57,042
HE DREW A REPRIMAND

146
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:59,669
AND WAS SENT TO
THE BOTTOM OF
THE PROMOTION LIST.

147
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,380
AND HE BLAMED YOU
FOR THAT?

148
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,048
YES.

149
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:04,549
HE HAD BEEN
AT THE ACADEMY

150
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:07,302
FOR AN UNUSUALLY
LONG TIME AS
AN INSTRUCTOR.

151
00:07:07,426 --> 00:07:08,762
AS A RESULT,
HE WAS LATE

152
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:10,931
IN BEING ASSIGNED
TO A STARSHIP.

153
00:07:11,056 --> 00:07:12,974
THE DELAY, HE FELT,
LOOKED BAD ON
HIS RECORD.

154
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,102
MY ACTION,
HE BELIEVED,
MADE THINGS WORSE.

155
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:16,436
COMMENT--

156
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:18,521
SERVICE RECORD
OF LIEUTENANT
COMMANDER FINNEY

157
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:20,148
TO BE APPENDED
THIS INQUIRY.

158
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:22,192
<i>NOTED.</i>

159
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:25,279
NOW, LET'S GET INTO
THE SPECIFICS OF
THE STORM, CAPTAIN.

160
00:07:25,404 --> 00:07:28,949
WEATHER SCAN
INDICATED AN ION STORM
DEAD AHEAD.

161
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:30,951
I SENT FINNEY
INTO THE POD.

162
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:32,202
WHY FINNEY?

163
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:33,536
HIS NAME WAS
AT THE TOP OF
THE DUTY ROSTER.

164
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:34,413
IF HE BLAMED YOU--

165
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:35,496
HE MAY HAVE
BLAMED ME

166
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:37,082
THAT HE NEVER ROSE
TO COMMAND A SHIP,

167
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:38,833
BUT I DON'T ASSIGN
JOBS ON THE BASIS
OF WHO BLAMES ME.

168
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:41,962
IT WAS
FINNEY'S TURN,
AND I ASSIGNED HIM.

169
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:45,632
HE HAD JUST
CHECKED IN WITH ME
FROM THE POD

170
00:07:45,757 --> 00:07:48,885
WHEN WE HIT
THE LEADING EDGE
OF THE STORM.

171
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:51,012
NOT TOO BAD
AT FIRST...

172
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:53,681
I SIGNALED
A YELLOW ALERT.

173
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:55,392
THEN WE BEGAN
ENCOUNTERING
PRESSURE,

174
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:58,019
VARIANT STRESS,
FORCE 7, THE WORKS.

175
00:07:58,145 --> 00:08:01,648
I FINALLY SIGNALED
A RED ALERT.

176
00:08:01,773 --> 00:08:05,986
FINNEY KNEW HE HAD
A MATTER OF SECONDS.

177
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:10,782
I GAVE HIM
THOSE SECONDS
AND MORE.

178
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:11,741
BUT...

179
00:08:11,866 --> 00:08:14,702
APPARENTLY
IT WASN'T ENOUGH.

180
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:17,414
THEN WHY CAPTAIN, DOES THE
COMPUTER LOG FROM YOUR SHIP

181
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:19,249
MADE AUTOMATICALLY
AT THE TIME,

182
00:08:19,374 --> 00:08:21,460
INDICATE THAT YOU WERE
STILL ON YELLOW ALERT
WHEN YOU JETTISONED

183
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:24,879
AND NOT ON RED?

184
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:27,799
I DON'T KNOW.

185
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,259
THERE'S BEEN
A MISTAKE.

186
00:08:29,384 --> 00:08:30,510
IT WOULD SEEM SO.

187
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:32,429
COULD THE COMPUTER
BE WRONG?

188
00:08:32,553 --> 00:08:34,514
MR. SPOCK IS
RUNNING A SURVEY
RIGHT NOW,

189
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:38,101
BUT THE ODDS ARE
NEXT TO IMPOSSIBLE.

190
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:41,980
STOP RECORDING.

191
00:08:42,105 --> 00:08:43,648
NOW, LOOK, JIM...

192
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:47,819
NOT ONE MAN
IN A MILLION

193
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,654
COULD DO WHAT YOU
AND I HAVE DONE--

194
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:52,032
COMMAND A STARSHIP.

195
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:53,700
A HUNDRED
DECISIONS A DAY,

196
00:08:53,825 --> 00:08:57,954
HUNDREDS OF LIVES
STAKED ON YOU MAKING
EVERY ONE OF THEM RIGHT.

197
00:08:58,079 --> 00:08:59,873
YOU'RE PLAYED OUT, JIM.

198
00:08:59,998 --> 00:09:00,790
EXHAUSTED.

199
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:02,250
IS THAT THE WAY
YOU SEE IT?

200
00:09:02,376 --> 00:09:03,877
THAT'S THE WAY
MY REPORT WILL READ
IF YOU COOPERATE.

201
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:07,214
PHYSICAL BREAKDOWN,
POSSIBLY EVEN MENTAL
COLLAPSE?

202
00:09:07,339 --> 00:09:08,465
POSSIBLY.

203
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:09,549
I'D BE ADMITTING
THAT A MAN DIED
BECAUSE--

204
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:10,758
ADMIT NOTHING.

205
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,719
SAY NOTHING.

206
00:09:12,844 --> 00:09:14,388
LET ME BURY
THE MATTER HERE AND NOW.

207
00:09:14,513 --> 00:09:16,515
NO STARSHIP CAPTAIN
HAS EVER STOOD TRIAL BEFORE,

208
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,099
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE THE FIRST.

209
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:19,600
BUT IF WHAT YOU SUSPECT
IS TRUE, THEN I'M
GUILTY.

210
00:09:19,726 --> 00:09:20,685
I SHOULD BE PUNISHED.

211
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:23,522
I'M THINKING
OF THE SERVICE.

212
00:09:23,646 --> 00:09:24,647
I WON'T
HAVE IT SMEARED.

213
00:09:24,772 --> 00:09:28,068
BY WHAT,
COMMODORE STONE?

214
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:30,028
ALL RIGHT...

215
00:09:30,153 --> 00:09:33,365
BY AN EVIDENT PERJURER
WHO IS EITHER COVERING UP
HIS BAD JUDGMENT,

216
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,615
HIS COWARDICE, OR
SOMETHING EVEN WORSE--

217
00:09:34,741 --> 00:09:36,993
THAT'S AS FAR
AS YOU GO, SIR.

218
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,329
I'M TELLING YOU
I WAS THERE
ON THE BRIDGE.

219
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,122
I KNOW WHAT
HAPPENED.
I KNOW WHAT I DID.

220
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:42,707
IT'S IN THE TRANSCRIPT,

221
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:45,668
AND COMPUTER TRANSCRIPTS
DON'T LIE.

222
