673
00:29:27,558 --> 00:29:31,186
NO. IT'S NOT
ALL BAD, MR. SPOCK.

674
00:29:31,311 --> 00:29:34,356
WHO KNOWS? YOU MAY BE
ABLE TO BEAT YOUR NEXT
CAPTAIN AT CHESS.

675
00:29:34,481 --> 00:29:35,399
KIRK OUT.

676
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:44,450
CHESS.

677
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:48,579
JAME.

678
00:29:48,704 --> 00:29:50,497
THIS IS LIEUTENANT
COMMANDER FINNEY'S
DAUGHTER.

679
00:29:50,623 --> 00:29:53,166
MR. COGLEY, WE'VE
GOT TO STOP THIS.

680
00:29:53,292 --> 00:29:55,502
MAKE HIM TAKE
A GROUND ASSIGNMENT.

681
00:29:55,628 --> 00:29:57,463
I REALIZE IT WASN'T
HIS FAULT.

682
00:29:57,588 --> 00:29:59,047
I WON'T MAKE
ANY TROUBLE.

683
00:29:59,172 --> 00:30:00,006
MAKE HIM CHANGE
HIS PLEA.

684
00:30:00,132 --> 00:30:01,717
IT'S TOO LATE
FOR THAT, JAME,

685
00:30:01,841 --> 00:30:04,052
BUT I'M GLAD YOU DON'T
BLAME ME ANYMORE
FOR WHAT HAPPENED.

686
00:30:04,177 --> 00:30:06,054
I WAS JUST SO UPSET
THAT NIGHT.

687
00:30:06,179 --> 00:30:07,097
I'M SORRY.

688
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:08,432
DON'T SAY ANY MORE.

689
00:30:08,557 --> 00:30:09,975
BUT I HAVE TO.

690
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:12,686
I NEVER REALIZED
HOW CLOSE YOU
AND DAD HAD BEEN

691
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:15,105
UNTIL I READ
THROUGH SOME OF THE
PAPERS HE WROTE,

692
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:18,525
LETTERS TO MOTHER
AND ME.

693
00:30:18,651 --> 00:30:21,903
I DON'T KNOW HOW
I EVER COULD'VE
THOUGHT THAT YOU...

694
00:30:22,028 --> 00:30:23,822
MR. COGLEY,

695
00:30:23,947 --> 00:30:25,532
RUINING JIM
WON'T CHANGE

696
00:30:25,658 --> 00:30:26,659
WHAT'S HAPPENED.

697
00:30:26,784 --> 00:30:28,661
THAT'S VERY COMMENDABLE,
MISS FINNEY,

698
00:30:28,786 --> 00:30:30,245
BUT MOST UNUSUAL.

699
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:32,414
AFTER ALL,
CAPTAIN KIRK IS ACCUSED

700
00:30:32,539 --> 00:30:34,166
OF CAUSING
YOUR FATHER'S DEATH,

701
00:30:34,291 --> 00:30:36,418
AND THE EVIDENCE
WOULD INDICATE HIS GUILT.

702
00:30:36,543 --> 00:30:38,003
I WAS JUST
THINKING OF JIM.

703
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:41,131
I KNOW,
AND I THANK YOU.

704
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:42,966
I HAVE TO GO AND CHANGE.
YOU READY?

705
00:30:43,091 --> 00:30:50,599
NO, BUT I MAY
BE GETTING READY.

706
00:30:50,724 --> 00:30:54,102
<i>BISHOP HALF LEVEL RIGHT.</i>

707
00:30:54,227 --> 00:30:55,729
WELL, I HAD TO SEE IT
TO BELIEVE IT.

708
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:56,605
EXPLAIN.

709
00:30:56,730 --> 00:30:57,815
THEY'RE ABOUT
TO LOP OFF

710
00:30:57,939 --> 00:30:59,358
THE CAPTAIN'S
PROFESSIONAL HEAD,

711
00:30:59,483 --> 00:31:01,401
AND YOU'RE SITTING
HERE PLAYING CHESS
WITH THE COMPUTER.

712
00:31:01,527 --> 00:31:03,153
THAT IS TRUE.

713
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:04,904
MR. SPOCK,
YOU'RE THE MOST
COLD-BLOODED MAN

714
00:31:05,030 --> 00:31:07,282
I'VE EVER KNOWN.

715
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:09,618
WHY, THANK YOU,
DOCTOR.

716
00:31:09,743 --> 00:31:12,830
I'VE JUST WON
MY FOURTH GAME.

717
00:31:12,954 --> 00:31:13,913
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

718
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:15,415
OBSERVE
FOR YOURSELF.

719
00:31:15,541 --> 00:31:18,377
ROOK TO KING'S
PAWN 4.

720
00:31:18,502 --> 00:31:21,213
<i>BISHOP</i>
<i>HALF LEVEL RIGHT.</i>

721
00:31:21,338 --> 00:31:24,966
NOW, THIS IS
THE COMPUTER'S MOVE.

722
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:30,556
AND NOW MINE.

723
00:31:30,681 --> 00:31:34,434
CHECKMATE.

724
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:36,562
MECHANICALLY, THE
COMPUTER IS FLAWLESS.

725
00:31:36,687 --> 00:31:38,313
THEREFORE, LOGICALLY,
ITS REPORT

726
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:40,607
OF THE CAPTAIN'S GUILT
IS INFALLIBLE.

727
00:31:40,733 --> 00:31:42,568
I COULD NOT
ACCEPT THAT, HOWEVER.

728
00:31:42,693 --> 00:31:44,361
SO YOU TESTED
THE PROGRAM BANK.

729
00:31:44,486 --> 00:31:45,779
EXACTLY.

730
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:48,156
I PROGRAMMED IT
MYSELF FOR CHESS
SOME MONTHS AGO.

731
00:31:48,281 --> 00:31:49,700
THE BEST
I SHOULD'VE BEEN
ABLE TO OBTAIN

732
00:31:49,825 --> 00:31:51,451
WAS A DRAW.

733
00:31:51,577 --> 00:31:54,204
WELL, WHY ARE YOU
JUST SITTING THERE?

734
00:31:54,329 --> 00:31:56,832
TRANSPORTER ROOM,
STAND BY. WE'RE
BEAMING DOWN.

735
00:32:03,171 --> 00:32:09,386
[RINGING BELL]

736
00:32:09,511 --> 00:32:10,846
COURT IS NOW
IN SESSION.

737
00:32:16,017 --> 00:32:17,477
THE BOARD WILL
ENTERTAIN MOTIONS

738
00:32:17,603 --> 00:32:19,396
BEFORE DELIVERING
ITS VERDICT.

739
00:32:19,521 --> 00:32:22,023
COUNSEL
FOR THE PROSECUTION?

740
00:32:22,148 --> 00:32:25,151
SIR, THE PROSECUTION
RESTS.

741
00:32:25,277 --> 00:32:29,030
COUNSEL
FOR THE DEFENSE?

742
00:32:29,155 --> 00:32:33,869
SIR...

743
00:32:33,993 --> 00:32:34,620
THE DEFENSE RESTS.

744
00:32:34,745 --> 00:32:36,288
[DOOR OPENS]

745
00:32:40,542 --> 00:32:43,044
MR. COGLEY.

746
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:44,630
MR. COGLEY!

747
00:32:44,755 --> 00:32:46,882
SIR,
SOME NEW EVIDENCE

748
00:32:47,006 --> 00:32:48,550
HAS JUST
BEEN BROUGHT
TO MY ATTENTION,

749
00:32:48,675 --> 00:32:50,009
AND I'D LIKE
TO ASK THE COURT--

750
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:51,303
OBJECTION!

751
00:32:51,428 --> 00:32:53,639
COUNSEL FOR
THE DEFENSE HAS
RESTED HIS CASE.

752
00:32:53,764 --> 00:32:55,599
OF WHAT NATURE
IS THIS EVIDENCE?

753
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:57,392
I CAN'T TELL YOU.
I HAVE TO SHOW YOU,
SIR.

754
00:32:57,517 --> 00:32:59,978
MR. COGLEY
IS WELL-KNOWN
FOR HIS THEATRICS.

755
00:33:00,103 --> 00:33:03,440
IS SAVING
AN INNOCENT MAN'S
CAREER A THEATRIC?

756
00:33:03,565 --> 00:33:05,525
COUNSELS WILL KINDLY
DIRECT THEIR REMARKS

757
00:33:05,651 --> 00:33:06,652
TO THE BENCH.

758
00:33:06,777 --> 00:33:08,862
I'D BE DELIGHTED
TO, SIR,

759
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:11,615
NOW THAT I'VE GOT
SOMETHING HUMAN
TO TALK ABOUT.

760
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:14,242
RIGHTS, SIR,
HUMAN RIGHTS--

761
00:33:14,367 --> 00:33:17,245
THE BIBLE, THE CODE
OF HAMMURABI

762
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:19,998
AND OF JUSTINIAN,
MAGNA CARTA,

763
00:33:20,123 --> 00:33:22,250
THE CONSTITUTION
OF THE UNITED
STATES,

764
00:33:22,375 --> 00:33:23,919
FUNDAMENTAL
DECLARATIONS

765
00:33:24,043 --> 00:33:25,921
OF THE MARTIAN
COLONIES.

766
00:33:26,045 --> 00:33:29,090
THE STATUTES
OF ALPHA 3--

767
00:33:29,215 --> 00:33:34,137
GENTLEMEN,
THESE DOCUMENTS
ALL SPEAK OF RIGHTS.

768
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:35,430
RIGHTS
OF THE ACCUSED

769
00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:37,516
TO A TRIAL
BY HIS PEERS,

770
00:33:37,641 --> 00:33:39,726
TO BE REPRESENTED
BY COUNSEL,

771
00:33:39,852 --> 00:33:41,645
THE RIGHTS OF
CROSS-EXAMINATION,

772
00:33:41,770 --> 00:33:44,272
BUT
MOST IMPORTANTLY,

773
00:33:44,397 --> 00:33:46,399
THE RIGHT
TO BE CONFRONTED

774
00:33:46,525 --> 00:33:48,401
BY THE WITNESSES
AGAINST HIM--

775
00:33:48,527 --> 00:33:50,570
A RIGHT TO
WHICH MY CLIENT
HAS BEEN DENIED.

776
00:33:50,696 --> 00:33:52,113
YOUR HONOR,
THAT IS RIDICULOUS.

777
00:33:52,238 --> 00:33:54,032
WE PRODUCED
THE WITNESSES IN COURT.

778
00:33:54,157 --> 00:33:55,951
MY LEARNED OPPONENT
HAD THE OPPORTUNITY

779
00:33:56,075 --> 00:33:57,369
TO SEE THEM,
CROSS-EXAMINE THEM--

780
00:33:57,494 --> 00:33:59,371
ALL BUT ONE!

781
00:33:59,496 --> 00:34:02,248
THE MOST
DEVASTATING WITNESS
AGAINST MY CLIENT

782
00:34:02,374 --> 00:34:04,042
IS NOT A HUMAN BEING.

783
00:34:04,167 --> 00:34:06,085
IT'S A MACHINE,

784
00:34:06,211 --> 00:34:07,880
AN INFORMATION
SYSTEM--

785
00:34:08,005 --> 00:34:09,965
THE COMPUTER LOG
OF THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

786
00:34:10,089 --> 00:34:13,092
AND I ASK THIS COURT
ADJOURN AND RECONVENE
ABOARD THAT VESSEL.

787
00:34:13,218 --> 00:34:14,093
I PROTEST,
YOUR HONOR.

788
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:17,305
AND I REPEAT,
I SPEAK OF RIGHTS.

789
00:34:17,430 --> 00:34:18,932
A MACHINE HAS NONE.

790
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:20,809
A MAN MUST.

791
00:34:20,934 --> 00:34:23,896
MY CLIENT HAS THE RIGHT
TO FACE HIS ACCUSER,

792
00:34:24,021 --> 00:34:26,648
AND IF YOU DO NOT
GRANT HIM THAT RIGHT,

793
00:34:26,773 --> 00:34:27,691
YOU HAVE BROUGHT US DOWN

794
00:34:27,816 --> 00:34:29,442
TO THE LEVEL
OF THE MACHINE.

795
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:33,864
INDEED, YOU HAVE ELEVATED
THAT MACHINE ABOVE US.

796
00:34:33,989 --> 00:34:36,700
I ASK THAT MY MOTION
BE GRANTED,

797
00:34:36,825 --> 00:34:38,744
AND MORE
THAN THAT, GENTLEMEN,

798
00:34:38,869 --> 00:34:41,038
IN THE NAME
OF HUMANITY,

799
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:43,373
FADING IN THE SHADOW
OF THE MACHINE,

800
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:45,166
I DEMAND IT.

801
00:34:45,291 --> 00:34:47,002
I DEMAND IT!

802
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:56,344
<i>CAPTAIN'S LOG,</i>
<i>STARDATE 2950.1.</i>

803
00:34:56,469 --> 00:34:57,930
<i>AFTER DUE</i>
<i>CONSIDERATION,</i>

804
00:34:58,055 --> 00:34:59,765
<i>THE GENERAL COURT-MARTIAL</i>
<i>HAS RECONVENED</i>

805
00:34:59,890 --> 00:35:01,474
<i>ON BOARD THE</i> ENTERPRISE.

806
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,727
HOW MANY GAMES OF CHESS
DID YOU WIN

807
00:35:03,852 --> 00:35:05,395
FROM THE COMPUTER,
MR. SPOCK?

808
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:07,230
FIVE IN ALL.

809
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:09,024
MAY THAT BE
CONSIDERED UNUSUAL?

810
00:35:09,190 --> 00:35:10,025
AFFIRMATIVE.

811
00:35:10,149 --> 00:35:11,818
WHY?

812
00:35:11,944 --> 00:35:14,112
I PERSONALLY
PROGRAMMED THE
COMPUTER FOR CHESS

813
00:35:14,237 --> 00:35:15,447
MONTHS AGO.

814
00:35:15,572 --> 00:35:17,699
I GAVE THE MACHINE
AN UNDERSTANDING
OF THE GAME

815
00:35:17,824 --> 00:35:19,534
EQUAL TO MY OWN.

816
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:21,954
THE COMPUTER CANNOT
MAKE AN ERROR.

817
00:35:22,079 --> 00:35:24,539
AND ASSUMING THAT
I DO NOT EITHER,

818
00:35:24,664 --> 00:35:26,583
THE BEST THAT COULD
NORMALLY
BE HOPED FOR

819
00:35:26,708 --> 00:35:29,252
WOULD BE STALEMATE
AFTER STALEMATE,

820
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:32,255
AND YET I BEAT
THE MACHINE
FIVE TIMES.

821
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:36,468
SOMEONE, EITHER
ACCIDENTALLY
OR DELIBERATELY,

822
00:35:36,593 --> 00:35:38,219
ADJUSTED
THE PROGRAMMING

823
00:35:38,344 --> 00:35:39,596
AND, THEREFORE,
THE MEMORY BANKS

824
00:35:39,721 --> 00:35:40,847
OF THAT COMPUTER.

825
00:35:43,058 --> 00:35:47,479
COULD THAT HAVE HAD AN EFFECT ON
THE VISUAL PLAYBACK WE SAW?

826
00:35:47,604 --> 00:35:48,647
OBJECT!

827
00:35:48,772 --> 00:35:51,650
THE WITNESS WOULD BE
MAKING A CONCLUSION.

828
00:35:51,775 --> 00:35:52,859
SUSTAINED.

829
00:35:52,985 --> 00:35:55,112
HYPOTHETICALLY,
MR. SPOCK.

830
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:57,072
HYPOTHETICALLY,
MISS SHAW,

831
00:35:57,196 --> 00:36:00,199
IF WHAT YOU SUGGEST
HAD BEEN DONE,

832
00:36:00,325 --> 00:36:03,202
IT WOULD BE BEYOND
THE CAPABILITIES
OF MOST MEN.

833
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:04,621
IS THAT TRUE?

834
00:36:04,746 --> 00:36:05,998
AFFIRMATIVE.

835
00:36:06,123 --> 00:36:09,793
WHAT MAN ABOARD SHIP
WOULD IT NOT
BE BEYOND?

836
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:11,336
THE CAPTAIN,
MYSELF,

837
00:36:11,461 --> 00:36:12,796
AND THE RECORDS
OFFICER.

838
00:36:12,921 --> 00:36:15,090
MM-HMM.
AND AT THE MOMENT,

839
00:36:15,214 --> 00:36:16,800
YOU HAVE
NO RECORDS OFFICER.

840
00:36:16,925 --> 00:36:17,884
AFFIRMATIVE.

841
00:36:18,010 --> 00:36:19,344
UNTIL HE WAS LOST,

842
00:36:19,469 --> 00:36:22,764
OUR RECORDS OFFICER
WAS LIEUTENANT
COMMANDER FINNEY.

843
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:24,808
CAPTAIN KIRK,

844
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:26,559
WILL YOU TELL
THE STEPS YOU TOOK

845
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:29,521
TO FIND MR. FINNEY
AFTER THE STORM?

846
00:36:29,646 --> 00:36:31,815
I INSTITUTED
A PHASE 1 SEARCH.

847
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:33,900
DESCRIBE
A PHASE 1 SEARCH.

848
00:36:34,026 --> 00:36:36,319
IT'S A PAINSTAKING,
THOROUGH ATTEMPT

849
00:36:36,444 --> 00:36:37,696
IN AND AROUND
THE SHIP

850
00:36:37,821 --> 00:36:39,280
TO FIND A MAN WHO'S
PRESUMABLY INJURED

851
00:36:39,405 --> 00:36:40,740
AND UNABLE
TO RESPOND.

852
00:36:40,866 --> 00:36:42,450
IT PRESUPPOSES,
DOES IT NOT,

853
00:36:42,575 --> 00:36:45,578
THAT A MAN WISHES
TO BE FOUND?

854
00:36:45,704 --> 00:36:46,579
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

855
00:36:46,705 --> 00:36:49,207
IF YOU START
A SEARCH
FOR A MAN,

856
00:36:49,332 --> 00:36:51,668
YOU ASSUME, DON'T YOU,
THAT HE WANTS
TO BE FOUND?

857
00:36:51,793 --> 00:36:53,003
HE'S NOT HIDING?

858
00:36:53,128 --> 00:36:54,921
YES.

859
00:36:55,047 --> 00:36:57,215
ON A SHIP
OF THIS SIZE,

860
00:36:57,340 --> 00:37:02,095
COULD A MAN
EVADE SUCH A SEARCH?

861
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:05,724
POSSIBLY.

862
00:37:05,849 --> 00:37:08,685
GENTLEMEN,
I SUBMIT TO YOU

863
00:37:08,810 --> 00:37:10,353
THAT LIEUTENANT
COMMANDER BEN FINNEY

864
00:37:10,478 --> 00:37:13,065
IS NOT DEAD.

865
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:15,150
MR. COGLEY, YOUR
WAITING FOR PROOF

866
00:37:15,274 --> 00:37:17,527
OF THE EXTRAORDINARY
STATEMENT YOU MADE
IN THE BRIEFING ROOM.

867
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:18,820
YOU SHALL HAVE IT,

868
00:37:18,945 --> 00:37:20,780
BUT FIRST I NEED THE
COOPERATION OF THIS COURT

869
00:37:20,906 --> 00:37:22,824
IN CONDUCTING
AN EXPERIMENT.

870
00:37:22,949 --> 00:37:24,159
CAPTAIN KIRK.

871
00:37:24,283 --> 00:37:26,327
GENTLEMEN,
FOR THE PURPOSES
OF THIS EXPERIMENT,

872
00:37:26,452 --> 00:37:28,121
IT'LL BE NECESSARY
FOR ALL PERSONNEL,

873
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:30,498
EXCEPT FOR MEMBERS
OF THE COURT AND
THE COMMAND CREW,

874
00:37:30,623 --> 00:37:32,042
TO LEAVE THE SHIP.

875
00:37:32,167 --> 00:37:34,836
I'M ORDERING
ALL OTHERS TO REPORT
TO THE TRANSPORTER ROOM.

876
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:36,213
INCLUDING MYSELF, SIR.

877
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:38,215
THIS COURT IS BY
NO MEANS ADJOURNED,
MR. COGLEY.

878
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:41,176
I HAVE AN ERRAND ASHORE
OF VITAL IMPORTANCE TO
THE PURPOSE OF THIS COURT,

879
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:42,969
AND I WILL RETURN.

880
00:37:43,095 --> 00:37:43,887
VERY WELL.

881
00:37:44,012 --> 00:37:45,764
THANK YOU, SIR.

882
00:37:45,889 --> 00:37:46,723
CAPTAIN, ARE YOU
MAINTAINING

883
00:37:46,848 --> 00:37:47,933
AN ENGINE CREW
ABOARD?

884
00:37:48,058 --> 00:37:49,350
OUR IMPULSE ENGINES
HAVE BEEN SHUT DOWN.

885
00:37:49,475 --> 00:37:51,103
WE'LL MAINTAIN ORBIT
BY MOMENTUM.

886
00:37:51,228 --> 00:37:52,979
AND WHEN THE ORBIT
BEGINS TO DECAY?

887
00:37:53,105 --> 00:37:55,107
WE HOPE TO BE FINISHED
LONG BEFORE THAT.

888
00:38:04,657 --> 00:38:05,575
READY, MR. SPOCK?

889
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:07,744
AFFIRMATIVE,
CAPTAIN.

890
00:38:07,869 --> 00:38:09,246
GENTLEMEN,
THIS COMPUTER

891
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:10,622
HAS AN AUDITORY
SENSOR.

892
00:38:10,747 --> 00:38:13,208
IT CAN, IN EFFECT,
HEAR SOUNDS.

893
00:38:13,332 --> 00:38:14,292
BY INSTALLING
A BOOSTER,

894
00:38:14,417 --> 00:38:15,710
WE CAN INCREASE
THAT CAPABILITY

895
00:38:15,835 --> 00:38:18,588
ON THE ORDER OF
1 TO THE 4th POWER.

896
00:38:18,713 --> 00:38:22,092
THE COMPUTER
SHOULD BE ABLE TO
BRING US EVERY SOUND

897
00:38:22,217 --> 00:38:23,760
OCCURRING
ON THE SHIP.

898
00:38:23,885 --> 00:38:24,886
<i>ALL PERSONNEL</i>

899
00:38:25,011 --> 00:38:26,930
<i>HAVE LEFT THE SHIP</i>
<i>AS ORDERED, SIR.</i>

900
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:29,515
DR. McCOY?

901
00:38:29,641 --> 00:38:31,893
ALL RIGHT,
MR. SPOCK.

902
00:38:32,018 --> 00:38:35,605
[LOUD BEATING]

903
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:46,992
TURN IT DOWN
A LITTLE.

904
00:38:47,117 --> 00:38:49,828
[VOLUME DECREASES]

905
00:38:52,914 --> 00:38:55,333
GENTLEMEN, THAT SOUND
IS CAUSED BY THE HEARTBEATS

906
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:58,753
OF ALL THE PEOPLE
ON BOARD THE SHIP.

907
00:38:58,878 --> 00:39:04,134
DR. McCOY WILL USE
THIS WHITE SOUND DEVICE

908
00:39:04,259 --> 00:39:06,719
TO MASK OUT
EACH PERSON'S HEARTBEAT

909
00:39:06,845 --> 00:39:08,054
SO THAT IT WILL BE
ELIMINATED

910
00:39:08,180 --> 00:39:09,347
FROM THE SOUNDS
WE'RE HEARING.

911
00:39:09,472 --> 00:39:11,099
FIRST, THE CAPTAIN.

912
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:16,646
MR. SPOCK.

913
00:39:35,623 --> 00:39:37,959
AND LASTLY, MYSELF.

914
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:41,838
THAT'S ALL OF US,

915
00:39:41,963 --> 00:39:43,798
EXCEPT FOR THE CREWMAN
IN THE TRANSPORTER ROOM.

916
00:39:43,923 --> 00:39:46,384
MR. SPOCK, ELIMINATE
HIS HEARTBEAT.

917
00:39:47,677 --> 00:39:48,887
[HEARTBEAT CONTINUES]

918
00:39:49,012 --> 00:39:51,639
THAT ACCOUNTS
FOR EVERYONE.

919
00:39:51,764 --> 00:39:55,060
[SINGLE HEART BEATS]

920
00:40:16,248 --> 00:40:18,083
FINNEY.

921
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:24,214
LOCALIZE THAT.

922
00:40:29,344 --> 00:40:30,929
"B" DECK.

923
00:40:31,054 --> 00:40:32,847
IN OR NEAR
ENGINEERING.

924
00:40:32,972 --> 00:40:35,850
SEAL OFF "B" DECK,
SECTIONS 18-Y
THROUGH 23-D.

925
00:40:35,975 --> 00:40:38,353
ACKNOWLEDGED.

926
00:40:38,477 --> 00:40:40,521
[BEEP]

927
00:40:47,112 --> 00:40:49,114
SO FINNEY IS ALIVE.

928
00:40:49,239 --> 00:40:50,907
IT WOULD SEEM SO.

929
00:40:51,032 --> 00:40:52,533
COMMODORE, THIS IS
MY PROBLEM.

930
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:57,414
I WOULD APPRECIATE IT IF
NO ONE LEFT THE BRIDGE.

931
00:40:57,538 --> 00:40:58,873
SAM COGLEY HAD GONE ASHORE

932
00:40:58,998 --> 00:41:00,417
<i>TO BRING JAME FINNEY</i>
<i>ON BOARD.</i>

933
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:01,918
<i>WE BOTH FELT</i>
<i>THAT JAME'S PRESENCE</i>

934
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:03,544
<i>WOULD MAKE FINNEY</i>
<i>EASIER TO HANDLE</i>

935
00:41:03,669 --> 00:41:05,922
<i>IN THE EVENT FINNEY</i>
<i>REALLY WERE ALIVE.</i>

936
00:41:06,047 --> 00:41:07,757
BEN.

937
00:41:09,801 --> 00:41:11,510
[KIRK]
<i>BEN FINNEY.</i>

938
00:41:17,642 --> 00:41:19,518
MR. SPOCK,
ENCOUNTERING
VARIANTS.

939
00:41:19,644 --> 00:41:20,228
COMPENSATE.

940
00:41:20,353 --> 00:41:21,271
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

941
00:41:21,396 --> 00:41:22,855
THE ORBIT IS
BEGINNING TO DECAY.

942
00:41:25,358 --> 00:41:27,944
BEN, WHERE ARE YOU?

943
00:41:40,165 --> 00:41:42,625
<i>HELLO, CAPTAIN!</i>

944
00:41:43,751 --> 00:41:46,712
<i>NOTHING TO SAY, CAPTAIN?</i>

945
00:41:49,966 --> 00:41:51,468
I'M GLAD
YOU'RE ALIVE.

946
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:53,178
<i>YOU MEAN</i>
<i>YOU'RE RELIEVED</i>

947
00:41:53,303 --> 00:41:55,013
<i>BECAUSE YOU THINK</i>
<i>YOUR CAREER</i>

948
00:41:55,138 --> 00:41:56,222
<i>IS SAVED.</i>

949
00:41:56,348 --> 00:41:58,557
<i>WELL, YOU'RE WRONG.</i>

950
00:42:06,399 --> 00:42:07,484
BEN!

951
00:42:09,694 --> 00:42:10,528
BEN, IT'S NOT
TOO LATE.

952
00:42:10,653 --> 00:42:12,238
WE CAN HELP YOU.

953
00:42:12,364 --> 00:42:14,991
<i>LIKE YOU HELPED ME</i>
<i>ALL ALONG, KEPT ME DOWN,</i>

954
00:42:15,116 --> 00:42:17,660
<i>ROBBED ME</i>
<i>OF MY OWN COMMAND?</i>

955
00:42:17,785 --> 00:42:19,120
<i>I'M A GOOD OFFICER.</i>

956
00:42:19,245 --> 00:42:21,122
<i>AS GOOD AS YOU.</i>

957
00:42:21,247 --> 00:42:23,666
<i>I'VE WATCHED YOU</i>
<i>FOR YEARS.</i>

958
00:42:23,791 --> 00:42:26,044
<i>THE GREAT CAPTAIN KIRK.</i>

959
00:42:31,716 --> 00:42:34,386
THEY TOLD YOU
TO DO IT TO ME.

960
00:42:34,511 --> 00:42:36,054
YOU ALL CONSPIRED
AGAINST ME.

961
00:42:36,179 --> 00:42:37,638
YOU RUINED ME,

962
00:42:37,763 --> 00:42:40,892
BUT YOU WON'T
DO IT ANYMORE.

963
00:42:41,017 --> 00:42:42,519
UHH.

964
00:42:50,276 --> 00:42:51,986
PUT THE PHASER
DOWN, BEN.

965
00:42:52,111 --> 00:42:55,114
OH, I WOULDN'T
KILL YOU, CAPTAIN.

966
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,615
YOUR OWN DEATH WOULD
MEAN TOO

967
00:42:56,741 --> 00:42:58,076
LITTLE TO YOU,

968
00:42:58,201 --> 00:42:59,660
BUT YOUR SHIP--

969
00:42:59,785 --> 00:43:00,870
WHAT ABOUT MY SHIP?

970
00:43:00,995 --> 00:43:02,330
IT'S DEAD.

971
00:43:02,455 --> 00:43:03,664
I'VE KILLED IT.

972
00:43:03,789 --> 00:43:04,582
I TAPPED OUT

973
00:43:04,707 --> 00:43:10,629
YOUR PRIMARY
ENERGY CIRCUITS.

974
00:43:10,755 --> 00:43:13,674
MR. SPOCK, WHAT'S
OUR ORBIT STATUS?

975
00:43:13,799 --> 00:43:14,633
DECAYING, CAPTAIN.

976
00:43:14,759 --> 00:43:15,927
VARIANTS
AT SECOND LEVEL

977
00:43:16,052 --> 00:43:18,596
DEPRECIATING
UNUSUALLY FAST.

978
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:20,306
YOU'RE OUT OF POWER.

979
00:43:20,432 --> 00:43:22,183
I KNOW
THIS SHIP, TOO.

980
00:43:22,308 --> 00:43:24,143
THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
SHOULD'VE BEEN MINE.

981
00:43:24,269 --> 00:43:26,479
YOU KEPT ME
FROM IT.

982
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:28,106
BEN...

983
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:32,610
WHY KILL
INNOCENT PEOPLE?

984
00:43:32,735 --> 00:43:33,611
INNOCENT?

985
00:43:33,736 --> 00:43:34,987
HA HA HA!

986
00:43:35,113 --> 00:43:37,532
OFFICERS AND GENTLEMEN,

987
00:43:37,656 --> 00:43:39,784
CAPTAINS ALL,

988
00:43:39,909 --> 00:43:44,539
EXCEPT FOR FINNEY
AND HIS ONE MISTAKE

989
00:43:44,663 --> 00:43:46,416
A LONG TIME AGO,

990
00:43:46,541 --> 00:43:47,875
BUT THEY
DON'T FORGET.

991
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:50,420
I LOGGED THE MISTAKE,
BEN. BLAME ME, NOT THEM.

992
00:43:50,545 --> 00:43:51,921
<i>BUT THEY ARE TO BLAME.</i>

993
00:43:52,046 --> 00:43:54,382
<i>ALL OF THEM.</i>

994
00:43:54,507 --> 00:43:57,760
I WAS A GOOD OFFICER.

995
00:43:57,885 --> 00:44:00,430
I REALLY WAS.

996
00:44:00,555 --> 00:44:04,225
I LOVED THE SERVICE
MORE THAN ANY MAN
EVER DID.

997
00:44:04,350 --> 00:44:07,312
MR. SPOCK,
WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF TIME.

998
00:44:07,437 --> 00:44:09,522
GENTLEMEN, IF YOU'LL
PLEASE HURRY TO THE
TRANSPORTER ROOM--

999
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:12,984
MR. SPOCK, THE COURT
HAS NOT YET REACHED
A VERDICT.

1000
00:44:13,109 --> 00:44:14,652
WE WILL HEAR
THIS WITNESS OUT.

1001
00:44:14,777 --> 00:44:15,820
VERY WELL, SIR.

1002
00:44:18,573 --> 00:44:20,325
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

1003
00:44:20,450 --> 00:44:22,118
YOU CAN BE HELPED,

1004
00:44:22,243 --> 00:44:23,620
BUT IF YOU KILL
ALL THOSE PEOPLE--

1005
00:44:23,744 --> 00:44:25,955
WHY SHOULDN'T I?

1006
00:44:26,080 --> 00:44:28,416
THEY KILLED ME,
DIDN'T THEY?

1007
00:44:28,541 --> 00:44:31,294
IT'S A FAIR TRADE.

1008
00:44:31,419 --> 00:44:35,006
IS JAME INCLUDED
IN THAT DEAL?

1009
00:44:35,131 --> 00:44:36,799
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

1010
00:44:36,924 --> 00:44:39,760
SHE'S ON BOARD
BY NOW.

1011
00:44:39,885 --> 00:44:41,429
YES. SHE'S ON BOARD.

1012
00:44:41,554 --> 00:44:44,265
WHY DID YOU DO THAT?

1013
00:44:44,390 --> 00:44:46,892
WHY DID YOU BRING
HER HERE?

1014
00:44:47,018 --> 00:44:48,520
I'LL KILL YOU!

1015
00:45:38,027 --> 00:45:39,111
<i>BEATEN AND SOBBING,</i>

1016
00:45:39,237 --> 00:45:40,988
<i>FINNEY TOLD ME WHERE</i>
<i>HE HAD SABOTAGED</i>

1017
00:45:41,113 --> 00:45:42,490
<i>THE PRIME ENERGY CIRCUITS.</i>

1018
00:45:42,615 --> 00:45:44,409
<i>THE DAMAGE HE HAD CAUSED</i>
<i>WAS CONSIDERABLE,</i>

1019
00:45:44,534 --> 00:45:45,742
<i>BUT NOT IRREPARABLE.</i>

1020
00:45:45,868 --> 00:45:48,120
<i>WITH LUCK,</i>
<i>I WOULD BE ABLE TO</i>
<i>EFFECT REPAIRS</i>

1021
00:45:48,246 --> 00:45:51,207
<i>BEFORE OUR ORBIT</i>
<i>DECAYED COMPLETELY.</i>

1022
00:46:24,949 --> 00:46:26,200
POWER RETURNING,
MR. SPOCK.

1023
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:28,202
UP 14 POINTS
AND RISING.

1024
00:46:28,327 --> 00:46:30,371
ACTIVATE PORT
IMPULSE ENGINES.

1025
00:46:30,496 --> 00:46:31,372
1/3 POWER.

1026
00:46:31,497 --> 00:46:32,957
1/3 POWER.

1027
00:46:39,756 --> 00:46:41,549
VARIANTS FADING.

1028
00:46:50,391 --> 00:46:52,977
ORBIT
STABILIZING.

1029
00:47:05,406 --> 00:47:07,283
ALL SECURE, SIR.

1030
00:47:13,414 --> 00:47:16,250
UNLESS
THE PROSECUTION
HAS AN OBJECTION,

1031
00:47:16,375 --> 00:47:18,670
I RULE THIS COURT
TO BE DISMISSED.

1032
00:47:18,795 --> 00:47:21,880
ABSOLUTELY
NO OBJECTION, SIR.

1033
00:47:41,192 --> 00:47:44,028
HOW LONG WILL IT BE
THIS TIME BEFORE
I SEE YOU AGAIN?

1034
00:47:44,153 --> 00:47:46,322
AT THE RISK
OF SOUNDING
LIKE A MYSTIC,

1035
00:47:46,447 --> 00:47:48,949
THAT DEPENDS
ON THE STARS.

1036
00:47:49,074 --> 00:47:51,952
SAM COGLEY ASKED
ME TO GIVE YOU
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

1037
00:47:52,077 --> 00:47:55,122
IT'S NOT A FIRST
EDITION OR ANYTHING--
JUST A BOOK.

1038
00:47:55,247 --> 00:47:57,709
SAM SAYS THAT
MAKES IT SPECIAL,
THOUGH.

1039
00:47:57,834 --> 00:47:59,627
I DIDN'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHANCE
TO THANK HIM.

1040
00:47:59,752 --> 00:48:01,838
HE'S BUSY
ON A CASE.

1041
00:48:01,962 --> 00:48:04,256
HE'S DEFENDING
BEN FINNEY.

1042
00:48:04,382 --> 00:48:05,800
HE SAYS HE'LL WIN.

1043
00:48:05,924 --> 00:48:09,094
I WOULDN'T BE
A BIT SURPRISED.

1044
00:48:09,220 --> 00:48:11,222
DO YOU THINK
IT WOULD CAUSE
A COMPLETE BREAKDOWN

1045
00:48:11,347 --> 00:48:12,557
OF DISCIPLINE

1046
00:48:12,682 --> 00:48:15,393
IF A LOWLY LIEUTENANT
KISSED A STARSHIP CAPTAIN

1047
00:48:15,518 --> 00:48:18,937
ON THE BRIDGE
OF HIS SHIP?

1048
00:48:19,063 --> 00:48:20,690
LET'S TRY.

1049
00:48:29,824 --> 00:48:30,949
SEE? NO CHANGE.

1050
00:48:31,075 --> 00:48:32,869
DISCIPLINE
GOES ON.

1051
00:48:32,993 --> 00:48:35,246
AND SO MUST
THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

1052
00:48:35,371 --> 00:48:37,623
GOODBYE, JIM.

1053
00:48:37,749 --> 00:48:39,709
GOODBYE, AREEL.

1054
00:48:39,834 --> 00:48:42,127
BETTER LUCK
NEXT TIME.

1055
00:48:42,253 --> 00:48:44,422
I HAD PRETTY GOOD LUCK
THIS TIME.

1056
00:48:44,547 --> 00:48:47,091
I LOST, DIDN'T I?

1057
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:08,529
SHE'S A VERY GOOD LAWYER.

1058
00:49:08,654 --> 00:49:09,572
OBVIOUSLY.

1059
00:49:09,697 --> 00:49:11,198
INDEED SHE IS.
